Note:
This file handles LSP server implementation and language server protocol.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Process LSP server implementation and language server protocol
- Handle LSP communication and LSP protocol management
- Manage LSP session management and LSP client communication
- Process LSP request handling and LSP response generation

This file is essential because of the following reasons:
- LSP server enables language server protocol integration and LSP support
- Proper LSP server handling ensures correct LSP protocol implementation
- LSP server support enables Runa compilation for LSP-integrated development

This file consists of the following functions/features/operation types:
- LSP server initialization and lifecycle management
- LSP message dispatch (initialize, shutdown, textDocument notifications)
- LSP request/response serialization over stdio transport
- Document store management for open text documents
- Capability negotiation during initialize handshake

Dependencies:
- Imports compiler/internal/string_utils.runa for string manipulation
- Imports compiler/internal/collections.runa for document storage
- Imports compiler/internal/memory_safety.runa for safe memory access
- Imports compiler/internal/owned_utils.runa for heap allocation
- Imports compiler/internal/buffer_utils.runa for I/O buffering
:End Note

Import "compiler/internal/string_utils.runa" as StringUtils
Import "compiler/internal/collections.runa" as Collections
Import "compiler/internal/memory_safety.runa" as MemorySafety
Import "compiler/internal/owned_utils.runa" as OwnedUtils
Import "compiler/internal/buffer_utils.runa" as BufferUtils
Import "compiler/internal/format_utils.runa" as FormatUtils

Note: ============================================================================
Note: LSP Server Structure
Note: ============================================================================

Note: LSPServer structure (56 bytes total, 7 fields x 8 bytes each)
Note: Layout:
Note:   offset 0:  input_stream (8 bytes) - Pointer to input stream buffer for reading client messages
Note:   offset 8:  output_stream (8 bytes) - Pointer to output stream buffer for writing responses
Note:   offset 16: initialized (8 bytes) - Boolean: 1 if server has completed initialize handshake
Note:   offset 24: capabilities (8 bytes) - Pointer to ServerCapabilities bitmask
Note:   offset 32: document_store (8 bytes) - Pointer to HashTable mapping URIs to document content
Note:   offset 40: shutdown_requested (8 bytes) - Boolean: 1 if shutdown request received
Note:   offset 48: next_request_id (8 bytes) - Monotonically increasing ID for server-initiated requests

Type called "LSPServer":
    input_stream as Integer
    output_stream as Integer
    initialized as Integer
    capabilities as Integer
    document_store as Integer
    shutdown_requested as Integer
    next_request_id as Integer
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: LSP Constants
Note: ============================================================================

Note: LSP message methods (used for dispatch)
Constant LSP_METHOD_INITIALIZE as Integer is 1
Constant LSP_METHOD_INITIALIZED as Integer is 2
Constant LSP_METHOD_SHUTDOWN as Integer is 3
Constant LSP_METHOD_EXIT as Integer is 4
Constant LSP_METHOD_TEXT_DOCUMENT_DID_OPEN as Integer is 10
Constant LSP_METHOD_TEXT_DOCUMENT_DID_CHANGE as Integer is 11
Constant LSP_METHOD_TEXT_DOCUMENT_DID_CLOSE as Integer is 12
Constant LSP_METHOD_TEXT_DOCUMENT_COMPLETION as Integer is 13
Constant LSP_METHOD_TEXT_DOCUMENT_HOVER as Integer is 14
Constant LSP_METHOD_TEXT_DOCUMENT_DEFINITION as Integer is 15
Constant LSP_METHOD_TEXT_DOCUMENT_REFERENCES as Integer is 16
Constant LSP_METHOD_TEXT_DOCUMENT_SYMBOLS as Integer is 17
Constant LSP_METHOD_TEXT_DOCUMENT_RENAME as Integer is 18
Constant LSP_METHOD_UNKNOWN as Integer is -1

Note: Server capability flags (bitmask)
Constant CAPABILITY_COMPLETION as Integer is 1
Constant CAPABILITY_HOVER as Integer is 2
Constant CAPABILITY_DEFINITION as Integer is 4
Constant CAPABILITY_REFERENCES as Integer is 8
Constant CAPABILITY_DOCUMENT_SYMBOLS as Integer is 16
Constant CAPABILITY_RENAME as Integer is 32
Constant CAPABILITY_DIAGNOSTICS as Integer is 64
Constant CAPABILITY_SEMANTIC_TOKENS as Integer is 128
Constant CAPABILITY_FORMATTING as Integer is 256

Note: LSP error codes per specification
Constant LSP_ERROR_PARSE as Integer is -32700
Constant LSP_ERROR_INVALID_REQUEST as Integer is -32600
Constant LSP_ERROR_METHOD_NOT_FOUND as Integer is -32601
Constant LSP_ERROR_INVALID_PARAMS as Integer is -32602
Constant LSP_ERROR_INTERNAL as Integer is -32603
Constant LSP_ERROR_SERVER_NOT_INITIALIZED as Integer is -32002
Constant LSP_ERROR_REQUEST_CANCELLED as Integer is -32800

Note: Content-Length header constant
Constant CONTENT_LENGTH_PREFIX_SIZE as Integer is 16
Constant HEADER_SEPARATOR_SIZE as Integer is 4

Note: Document sync kind
Constant TEXT_DOCUMENT_SYNC_NONE as Integer is 0
Constant TEXT_DOCUMENT_SYNC_FULL as Integer is 1
Constant TEXT_DOCUMENT_SYNC_INCREMENTAL as Integer is 2

Note: LSP result codes
Constant LSP_SUCCESS as Integer is 0
Constant LSP_FAILED as Integer is -1

Note: ============================================================================
Note: LSP Server Creation and Lifecycle
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "create_lsp_server" returns Integer:
    Note: Create and initialize a new LSP server instance
    Note: Allocates LSPServer structure (56 bytes) on the owned heap
    Note: Initializes the document store as an empty hash table
    Note: Sets all capability flags for Runa language support
    Note: Returns pointer to LSPServer, or 0 on allocation failure

    Note: Allocate LSPServer structure (7 fields x 8 bytes = 56 bytes)
    Let server be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 56
    If server is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Allocate input stream buffer (8192 bytes for reading LSP messages)
    Let input_buf be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 8192
    If input_buf is equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with server
        Return 0
    End If
    Let dummy1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with server, 0, input_buf

    Note: Allocate output stream buffer (8192 bytes for writing LSP responses)
    Let output_buf be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 8192
    If output_buf is equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free1 be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with input_buf
        Let dummy_free2 be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with server
        Return 0
    End If
    Let dummy2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with server, 8, output_buf

    Note: Server is not yet initialized (handshake pending)
    Let dummy3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with server, 16, 0

    Note: Set server capabilities bitmask for all Runa-supported features
    Note: Runa LSP supports: completion, hover, go-to-definition, references,
    Note: document symbols, rename, diagnostics, semantic tokens, and formatting
    Let all_capabilities be CAPABILITY_COMPLETION
    Set all_capabilities to all_capabilities plus CAPABILITY_HOVER
    Set all_capabilities to all_capabilities plus CAPABILITY_DEFINITION
    Set all_capabilities to all_capabilities plus CAPABILITY_REFERENCES
    Set all_capabilities to all_capabilities plus CAPABILITY_DOCUMENT_SYMBOLS
    Set all_capabilities to all_capabilities plus CAPABILITY_RENAME
    Set all_capabilities to all_capabilities plus CAPABILITY_DIAGNOSTICS
    Set all_capabilities to all_capabilities plus CAPABILITY_SEMANTIC_TOKENS
    Set all_capabilities to all_capabilities plus CAPABILITY_FORMATTING
    Let dummy4 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with server, 24, all_capabilities

    Note: Create document store hash table for tracking open documents
    Note: Key: document URI string pointer, Value: document content pointer
    Note: Initial capacity of 64 buckets provides good distribution for typical workspaces
    Let doc_store be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 48
    If doc_store is equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free3 be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with output_buf
        Let dummy_free4 be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with input_buf
        Let dummy_free5 be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with server
        Return 0
    End If
    Note: Initialize document store fields: buckets, size, capacity
    Let bucket_array be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 512
    If bucket_array is equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free6 be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with doc_store
        Let dummy_free7 be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with output_buf
        Let dummy_free8 be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with input_buf
        Let dummy_free9 be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with server
        Return 0
    End If
    Note: Zero out bucket array (64 buckets x 8 bytes = 512 bytes)
    Let zero_idx be 0
    While zero_idx is less than 64:
        Let dummy_zero be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with bucket_array, zero_idx multiplied by 8, 0
        Set zero_idx to zero_idx plus 1
    End While
    Let dummy_ds1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with doc_store, 0, bucket_array
    Let dummy_ds2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with doc_store, 8, 0
    Let dummy_ds3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with doc_store, 16, 64
    Let dummy5 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with server, 32, doc_store

    Note: No shutdown requested yet
    Let dummy6 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with server, 40, 0

    Note: Initialize request ID counter to 1 (0 is reserved for null)
    Let dummy7 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with server, 48, 1

    Return server
End Process

Process called "start_server" takes server as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Start the LSP server main loop
    Note: Reads messages from stdin using Content-Length framing (LSP base protocol)
    Note: Dispatches each message via handle_message
    Note: Continues until exit notification or shutdown_requested is set
    Note: Returns LSP_SUCCESS (0) on clean exit, LSP_FAILED (-1) on error

    If server is equal to 0:
        Return LSP_FAILED
    End If

    Note: Main message loop
    Let running be 1
    While running is equal to 1:
        Note: Check if shutdown was requested
        Let shutdown_flag be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with server, 40
        If shutdown_flag is equal to 1:
            Set running to 0
        End If

        If running is equal to 1:
            Note: Read Content-Length header from input stream
            Note: LSP base protocol: "Content-Length: <length>\r\n\r\n<body>"
            Let input_buf be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with server, 0
            If input_buf is equal to 0:
                Set running to 0
            End If

            If running is equal to 1:
                Note: Read the header line to extract message length
                Note: Parse Content-Length value from header bytes
                Let content_length be proc read_content_length from input_buf
                If content_length is less than 0:
                    Note: Invalid or missing Content-Length means protocol error or stream closed
                    Set running to 0
                End If

                If running is equal to 1:
                    If content_length is equal to 0:
                        Note: Zero-length content indicates stream end
                        Set running to 0
                    End If

                    If running is equal to 1:
                        Note: Read the message body of content_length bytes
                        Let message_body be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with content_length plus 1
                        If message_body is equal to 0:
                            Set running to 0
                        End If

                        If running is equal to 1:
                            Note: Read content_length bytes from input into message_body
                            Let bytes_read be proc read_message_body from input_buf, message_body, content_length
                            If bytes_read is not equal to content_length:
                                Let dummy_free_msg be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with message_body
                                Set running to 0
                            End If

                            If running is equal to 1:
                                Note: Null-terminate the message body
                                Let dummy_term be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with message_body, content_length, 0

                                Note: Dispatch the message
                                Let dispatch_result be proc handle_message with server, message_body, content_length
                                Let dummy_free_body be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with message_body

                                Note: Check if the dispatched message was an exit notification
                                Let shutdown_after be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with server, 40
                                If shutdown_after is equal to 1:
                                    Set running to 0
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While

    Return LSP_SUCCESS
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Internal Helper - Read Content-Length from LSP Base Protocol Header
Note: ============================================================================

Private Process called "read_content_length" takes input_buf as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse the Content-Length header from the LSP base protocol
    Note: Reads bytes from input_buf looking for "Content-Length: <digits>\r\n\r\n"
    Note: Returns the integer content length, or -1 on parse failure
    Note: The LSP specification requires Content-Length as the only mandatory header

    If input_buf is equal to 0:
        Return -1
    End If

    Note: Read header bytes character by character
    Note: Look for pattern: "Content-Length: " followed by digits followed by "\r\n\r\n"
    Let header_buf be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 256
    If header_buf is equal to 0:
        Return -1
    End If

    Let pos be 0
    Let found_end be 0
    Let max_header_size be 255

    Note: Read bytes until we find the double CRLF that ends the header section
    While found_end is equal to 0:
        If pos is greater than max_header_size:
            Note: Header too large, protocol error
            Let dummy_free be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with header_buf
            Return -1
        End If

        Note: Read one byte from the input buffer
        Let byte_val be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with input_buf, pos
        Let dummy_store be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with header_buf, pos, byte_val

        Note: Check for end of header (\r\n\r\n sequence)
        If pos is greater than 2:
            Let prev3 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with header_buf, pos minus 3
            Let prev2 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with header_buf, pos minus 2
            Let prev1 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with header_buf, pos minus 1
            If prev3 is equal to 13:
                If prev2 is equal to 10:
                    If prev1 is equal to 13:
                        If byte_val is equal to 10:
                            Set found_end to 1
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Set pos to pos plus 1
    End While

    Note: Parse the content length value from the header
    Note: Skip "Content-Length: " prefix (16 characters)
    Let digit_start be CONTENT_LENGTH_PREFIX_SIZE
    Let content_length be 0
    Let digit_pos be digit_start

    While digit_pos is less than pos:
        Let digit_byte be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with header_buf, digit_pos
        Note: Check if byte is a digit (ASCII 48-57)
        If digit_byte is greater than 47:
            If digit_byte is less than 58:
                Set content_length to content_length multiplied by 10
                Set content_length to content_length plus digit_byte minus 48
            End If
        End If
        Note: Stop at CR (13) which starts the line ending
        If digit_byte is equal to 13:
            Set digit_pos to pos
        End If
        Set digit_pos to digit_pos plus 1
    End While

    Let dummy_free_hdr be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with header_buf
    Return content_length
End Process

Private Process called "read_message_body" takes input_buf as Integer, message_body as Integer, content_length as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Read exactly content_length bytes from input buffer into message_body
    Note: Returns number of bytes successfully read

    If input_buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If message_body is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If content_length is less than 1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Copy content_length bytes from input to message body
    Let idx be 0
    While idx is less than content_length:
        Let byte_val be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with input_buf, idx
        Let dummy_write be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with message_body, idx, byte_val
        Set idx to idx plus 1
    End While

    Return content_length
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Message Dispatch
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "handle_message" takes server as Integer, message as Integer, length as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse and dispatch an incoming LSP JSON-RPC message
    Note: Identifies the method field and routes to the appropriate handler
    Note: Returns LSP_SUCCESS on successful dispatch, LSP_FAILED on error
    Note:
    Note: The method string is identified by scanning the JSON for the "method" key
    Note: and comparing against known LSP method strings. Each method routes to its
    Note: dedicated handler process.

    If server is equal to 0:
        Return LSP_FAILED
    End If
    If message is equal to 0:
        Return LSP_FAILED
    End If

    Note: Extract the method from the JSON-RPC message
    Note: Scan for "method" key in the JSON payload
    Let method_id be proc identify_method from message, length
    If method_id is equal to LSP_METHOD_UNKNOWN:
        Note: Unknown method - send method not found error for requests
        Note: Notifications (no id) can be silently ignored per spec
        Let has_id be proc json_has_field from message, length, 105, 100
        If has_id is equal to 1:
            Let request_id be proc extract_request_id from message, length
            Let dummy_err be proc send_error_response with server, request_id, LSP_ERROR_METHOD_NOT_FOUND, 0
        End If
        Return LSP_SUCCESS
    End If

    Note: Check server initialization state
    Note: Before initialize, only initialize and exit are allowed
    Let is_initialized be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with server, 16
    If is_initialized is equal to 0:
        If method_id is not equal to LSP_METHOD_INITIALIZE:
            If method_id is not equal to LSP_METHOD_EXIT:
                Let has_id2 be proc json_has_field from message, length, 105, 100
                If has_id2 is equal to 1:
                    Let request_id2 be proc extract_request_id from message, length
                    Let dummy_err2 be proc send_error_response with server, request_id2, LSP_ERROR_SERVER_NOT_INITIALIZED, 0
                End If
                Return LSP_SUCCESS
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Note: Route to appropriate handler based on method
    If method_id is equal to LSP_METHOD_INITIALIZE:
        Let result be proc handle_initialize with server, message, length
        Return result
    End If
    If method_id is equal to LSP_METHOD_INITIALIZED:
        Note: initialized notification - no response needed, server is ready
        Return LSP_SUCCESS
    End If
    If method_id is equal to LSP_METHOD_SHUTDOWN:
        Set result to proc handle_shutdown with server, message, length
        Return result
    End If
    If method_id is equal to LSP_METHOD_EXIT:
        Note: Mark server for exit
        Let dummy_exit be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with server, 40, 1
        Return LSP_SUCCESS
    End If
    If method_id is equal to LSP_METHOD_TEXT_DOCUMENT_DID_OPEN:
        Set result to proc handle_text_document_did_open with server, message, length
        Return result
    End If
    If method_id is equal to LSP_METHOD_TEXT_DOCUMENT_DID_CHANGE:
        Set result to proc handle_text_document_did_change with server, message, length
        Return result
    End If
    If method_id is equal to LSP_METHOD_TEXT_DOCUMENT_DID_CLOSE:
        Set result to proc handle_text_document_did_close with server, message, length
        Return result
    End If

    Return LSP_SUCCESS
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Internal Helpers - JSON Field Operations
Note: ============================================================================

Private Process called "identify_method" takes message as Integer, length as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Identify the LSP method from a JSON-RPC message
    Note: Scans the raw JSON bytes for the "method" key and compares the value
    Note: against known LSP method strings
    Note: Returns the method constant ID, or LSP_METHOD_UNKNOWN

    If message is equal to 0:
        Return LSP_METHOD_UNKNOWN
    End If

    Note: Scan for "method" key in JSON
    Note: Look for the byte sequence: "method":"
    Note: ASCII: m=109, e=101, t=116, h=104, o=111, d=100
    Let scan_pos be 0
    Let method_start be -1

    While scan_pos is less than length:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with message, scan_pos
        Note: Look for 'm' followed by "ethod"
        If ch is equal to 109:
            If scan_pos + 6 is less than length:
                Let ch1 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with message, scan_pos + 1
                Let ch2 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with message, scan_pos + 2
                Let ch3 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with message, scan_pos + 3
                Let ch4 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with message, scan_pos + 4
                Let ch5 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with message, scan_pos + 5
                If ch1 is equal to 101:
                    If ch2 is equal to 116:
                        If ch3 is equal to 104:
                            If ch4 is equal to 111:
                                If ch5 is equal to 100:
                                    Note: Found "method" - now find the value string start
                                    Let val_scan be scan_pos + 6
                                    While val_scan is less than length:
                                        Let vc be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with message, val_scan
                                        Note: Look for opening quote of value (ASCII 34 = ")
                                        If vc is equal to 34:
                                            Set method_start to val_scan + 1
                                            Set val_scan to length
                                        End If
                                        Set val_scan to val_scan + 1
                                    End While
                                    Set scan_pos to length
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set scan_pos to scan_pos + 1
    End While

    If method_start is equal to -1:
        Return LSP_METHOD_UNKNOWN
    End If

    Note: Extract method string and compare against known methods
    Note: Read characters from method_start until closing quote
    Let method_len be 0
    Let end_scan be method_start
    While end_scan is less than length:
        Let end_ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with message, end_scan
        If end_ch is equal to 34:
            Set method_len to end_scan - method_start
            Set end_scan to length
        End If
        Set end_scan to end_scan + 1
    End While

    Note: Compare method string against known LSP methods
    Note: "initialize" = 10 chars
    If method_len is equal to 10:
        Let m0 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with message, method_start
        Let m1 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with message, method_start + 1
        Note: i=105, n=110
        If m0 is equal to 105:
            If m1 is equal to 110:
                Return LSP_METHOD_INITIALIZE
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Note: "initialized" = 11 chars
    If method_len is equal to 11:
        Set m0 to proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with message, method_start
        If m0 is equal to 105:
            Return LSP_METHOD_INITIALIZED
        End If
    End If

    Note: "shutdown" = 8 chars
    If method_len is equal to 8:
        Set m0 to proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with message, method_start
        Set m1 to proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with message, method_start + 1
        Note: s=115, h=104
        If m0 is equal to 115:
            If m1 is equal to 104:
                Return LSP_METHOD_SHUTDOWN
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Note: "exit" = 4 chars
    If method_len is equal to 4:
        Set m0 to proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with message, method_start
        Note: e=101
        If m0 is equal to 101:
            Return LSP_METHOD_EXIT
        End If
    End If

    Note: "textDocument/didOpen" = 20 chars
    If method_len is equal to 20:
        Set m0 to proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with message, method_start
        Note: t=116
        If m0 is equal to 116:
            Let m14 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with message, method_start + 14
            Note: 'O' = 79 (didOpen)
            If m14 is equal to 79:
                Return LSP_METHOD_TEXT_DOCUMENT_DID_OPEN
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Note: "textDocument/didChange" = 22 chars
    If method_len is equal to 22:
        Set m0 to proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with message, method_start
        If m0 is equal to 116:
            Return LSP_METHOD_TEXT_DOCUMENT_DID_CHANGE
        End If
    End If

    Note: "textDocument/didClose" = 21 chars
    If method_len is equal to 21:
        Set m0 to proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with message, method_start
        If m0 is equal to 116:
            Return LSP_METHOD_TEXT_DOCUMENT_DID_CLOSE
        End If
    End If

    Return LSP_METHOD_UNKNOWN
End Process

Private Process called "json_has_field" takes message as Integer, length as Integer, char1 as Integer, char2 as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if the JSON message contains a field whose key starts with the two given ASCII characters
    Note: Used to detect presence of "id" field (char1=105 'i', char2=100 'd')
    Note: Returns 1 if found, 0 if not

    If message is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let scan be 0
    While scan is less than length - 1:
        Let c1 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with message, scan
        Let c2 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with message, scan + 1
        If c1 is equal to char1:
            If c2 is equal to char2:
                Return 1
            End If
        End If
        Set scan to scan + 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

Private Process called "extract_request_id" takes message as Integer, length as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Extract the numeric request ID from a JSON-RPC message
    Note: Scans for "id": followed by a number
    Note: Returns the integer ID, or 0 if not found

    If message is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Scan for "id" key - look for "id":
    Note: ASCII: i=105, d=100
    Let scan be 0
    Let id_value_start be -1

    While scan is less than length - 3:
        Let c0 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with message, scan
        Let c1 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with message, scan + 1
        Let c2 be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with message, scan + 2
        Note: Look for quote-i-d-quote pattern: "id"
        If c0 is equal to 34:
            If c1 is equal to 105:
                If c2 is equal to 100:
                    Note: Skip past "id" and find the colon then the value
                    Let after_key be scan + 3
                    While after_key is less than length:
                        Let ac be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with message, after_key
                        Note: Skip colon (58), spaces (32), quotes
                        If ac is greater than 47:
                            If ac is less than 58:
                                Set id_value_start to after_key
                                Set after_key to length
                            End If
                        End If
                        Set after_key to after_key + 1
                    End While
                    Set scan to length
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set scan to scan + 1
    End While

    If id_value_start is equal to -1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Parse the numeric ID value
    Let id_value be 0
    Let digit_pos be id_value_start
    While digit_pos is less than length:
        Let dch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with message, digit_pos
        If dch is greater than 47:
            If dch is less than 58:
                Set id_value to id_value multiplied by 10
                Set id_value to id_value + dch - 48
            End If
        Otherwise:
            Set digit_pos to length
        End If
        Set digit_pos to digit_pos + 1
    End While

    Return id_value
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: LSP Protocol Handlers
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "handle_initialize" takes server as Integer, message as Integer, length as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Handle the "initialize" request from the client
    Note: Per LSP spec, the server MUST respond with ServerCapabilities
    Note: The server MUST NOT respond to any other request before initialize completes
    Note: Returns LSP_SUCCESS on success, LSP_FAILED on error

    If server is equal to 0:
        Return LSP_FAILED
    End If

    Note: Extract the request ID for the response
    Let request_id be proc extract_request_id from message, length

    Note: Mark server as initialized
    Let dummy_init be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with server, 16, 1

    Note: Build the initialize response with server capabilities
    Note: Response JSON structure:
    Note: {"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":<id>,"result":{"capabilities":{
    Note:   "textDocumentSync":1,
    Note:   "completionProvider":{"triggerCharacters":[".","@"]},
    Note:   "hoverProvider":true,
    Note:   "definitionProvider":true,
    Note:   "referencesProvider":true,
    Note:   "documentSymbolProvider":true,
    Note:   "renameProvider":true,
    Note:   "semanticTokensProvider":{"full":true,"legend":{...}}
    Note: }}}

    Note: Allocate response buffer (2048 bytes for capability response)
    Let response_buf be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 2048
    If response_buf is equal to 0:
        Return LSP_FAILED
    End If

    Note: Build JSON response manually (byte-by-byte construction)
    Note: {"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":
    Let response_json be proc build_initialize_response from request_id
    If response_json is equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with response_buf
        Return LSP_FAILED
    End If

    Note: Send the response
    Let send_result be proc send_response with server, response_json
    Return send_result
End Process

Process called "handle_shutdown" takes server as Integer, message as Integer, length as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Handle the "shutdown" request
    Note: Per LSP spec, the server should prepare to exit but not exit yet
    Note: Must respond with null result
    Note: After shutdown, only "exit" notification is valid

    If server is equal to 0:
        Return LSP_FAILED
    End If

    Note: Extract request ID
    Let request_id be proc extract_request_id from message, length

    Note: Mark shutdown as requested
    Let dummy_sd be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with server, 40, 1

    Note: Build null result response: {"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":<id>,"result":null}
    Let response be proc build_null_response from request_id
    If response is not equal to 0:
        Let send_result be proc send_response with server, response
        Return send_result
    End If

    Return LSP_SUCCESS
End Process

Process called "handle_text_document_did_open" takes server as Integer, message as Integer, length as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Handle textDocument/didOpen notification
    Note: The client sends this when a document is opened
    Note: We store the document URI and content in the document store
    Note: This is a notification - no response is sent

    If server is equal to 0:
        Return LSP_FAILED
    End If

    Note: Extract the document URI from the textDocument.uri field
    Let uri_ptr be proc extract_text_document_uri from message, length
    If uri_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return LSP_FAILED
    End If

    Note: Extract the document text from the textDocument.text field
    Let text_ptr be proc extract_text_document_text from message, length
    If text_ptr is equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free_uri be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with uri_ptr
        Return LSP_FAILED
    End If

    Note: Store the document in the document store
    Note: The document store is a hash table at offset 32 of the server
    Let doc_store be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with server, 32
    If doc_store is not equal to 0:
        Note: Create a document entry (16 bytes: uri pointer + content pointer)
        Let doc_entry be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 16
        If doc_entry is not equal to 0:
            Let dummy_set_uri be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with doc_entry, 0, uri_ptr
            Let dummy_set_text be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with doc_entry, 8, text_ptr

            Note: Insert into document store using URI hash as key
            Let uri_hash be proc hash_string_bytes from uri_ptr
            Let capacity be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc_store, 16
            Let bucket_idx be uri_hash
            Note: modulo by capacity to get bucket index
            If capacity is greater than 0:
                While bucket_idx is greater than capacity - 1:
                    Set bucket_idx to bucket_idx - capacity
                End While
            End If
            Let buckets be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc_store, 0
            Let dummy_insert be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buckets, bucket_idx multiplied by 8, doc_entry

            Note: Increment size counter
            Let current_size be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc_store, 8
            Let dummy_inc_size be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with doc_store, 8, current_size + 1
        End If
    End If

    Return LSP_SUCCESS
End Process

Process called "handle_text_document_did_change" takes server as Integer, message as Integer, length as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Handle textDocument/didChange notification
    Note: Updates the stored document content with the new text
    Note: Uses full document sync (TEXT_DOCUMENT_SYNC_FULL) - replaces entire content
    Note: This is a notification - no response is sent

    If server is equal to 0:
        Return LSP_FAILED
    End If

    Note: Extract the document URI
    Let uri_ptr be proc extract_text_document_uri from message, length
    If uri_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return LSP_FAILED
    End If

    Note: Extract the new document text from contentChanges[0].text
    Let new_text_ptr be proc extract_change_text from message, length
    If new_text_ptr is equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free_uri be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with uri_ptr
        Return LSP_FAILED
    End If

    Note: Find existing document in the store and update its content
    Let doc_store be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with server, 32
    If doc_store is not equal to 0:
        Let uri_hash be proc hash_string_bytes from uri_ptr
        Let capacity be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc_store, 16
        Let bucket_idx be uri_hash
        If capacity is greater than 0:
            While bucket_idx is greater than capacity - 1:
                Set bucket_idx to bucket_idx - capacity
            End While
        End If
        Let buckets be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc_store, 0
        Let doc_entry be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with buckets, bucket_idx multiplied by 8

        If doc_entry is not equal to 0:
            Note: Free old text content
            Let old_text be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc_entry, 8
            If old_text is not equal to 0:
                Let dummy_free_old be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with old_text
            End If
            Note: Set new text content
            Let dummy_set_new be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with doc_entry, 8, new_text_ptr
        Otherwise:
            Note: Document not found - create new entry (handles race condition)
            Let doc_entry_new be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 16
            If doc_entry_new is not equal to 0:
                Let dummy_new_uri be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with doc_entry_new, 0, uri_ptr
                Let dummy_new_text be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with doc_entry_new, 8, new_text_ptr
                Let dummy_ins be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buckets, bucket_idx multiplied by 8, doc_entry_new
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Return LSP_SUCCESS
End Process

Process called "handle_text_document_did_close" takes server as Integer, message as Integer, length as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Handle textDocument/didClose notification
    Note: Removes the document from the document store and frees its memory
    Note: This is a notification - no response is sent

    If server is equal to 0:
        Return LSP_FAILED
    End If

    Note: Extract the document URI
    Let uri_ptr be proc extract_text_document_uri from message, length
    If uri_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return LSP_FAILED
    End If

    Note: Find and remove the document from the store
    Let doc_store be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with server, 32
    If doc_store is not equal to 0:
        Let uri_hash be proc hash_string_bytes from uri_ptr
        Let capacity be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc_store, 16
        Let bucket_idx be uri_hash
        If capacity is greater than 0:
            While bucket_idx is greater than capacity - 1:
                Set bucket_idx to bucket_idx - capacity
            End While
        End If
        Let buckets be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc_store, 0
        Let doc_entry be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with buckets, bucket_idx multiplied by 8

        If doc_entry is not equal to 0:
            Note: Free document URI
            Let stored_uri be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc_entry, 0
            If stored_uri is not equal to 0:
                Let dummy_free_suri be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with stored_uri
            End If
            Note: Free document content
            Let stored_text be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc_entry, 8
            If stored_text is not equal to 0:
                Let dummy_free_stext be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with stored_text
            End If
            Note: Free the entry itself
            Let dummy_free_entry be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with doc_entry
            Note: Clear the bucket slot
            Let dummy_clear_slot be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buckets, bucket_idx multiplied by 8, 0

            Note: Decrement size counter
            Let current_size be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with doc_store, 8
            If current_size is greater than 0:
                Let dummy_dec_size be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with doc_store, 8, current_size - 1
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Note: Free the extracted URI
    Let dummy_free_uri2 be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with uri_ptr

    Return LSP_SUCCESS
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Response Construction and Sending
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "send_response" takes server as Integer, response_json as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Send an LSP response message to the client via stdout
    Note: Wraps the JSON body with Content-Length header per LSP base protocol
    Note: Format: "Content-Length: <length>\r\n\r\n<json_body>"
    Note: Returns LSP_SUCCESS on success, LSP_FAILED on error

    If server is equal to 0:
        Return LSP_FAILED
    End If
    If response_json is equal to 0:
        Return LSP_FAILED
    End If

    Note: Calculate the length of the response JSON body
    Let json_length be proc measure_string_length from response_json
    If json_length is equal to 0:
        Return LSP_FAILED
    End If

    Note: Build the Content-Length header
    Note: "Content-Length: " + digits + "\r\n\r\n"
    Let output_buf be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with server, 8
    If output_buf is equal to 0:
        Return LSP_FAILED
    End If

    Note: Write "Content-Length: " header prefix
    Let header_bytes be proc write_content_length_header from output_buf, json_length
    If header_bytes is equal to 0:
        Return LSP_FAILED
    End If

    Note: Write the JSON body after the header
    Let body_write be proc write_bytes from output_buf, header_bytes, response_json, json_length

    Note: Free the response JSON buffer
    Let dummy_free_json be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with response_json

    Return LSP_SUCCESS
End Process

Process called "send_notification" takes server as Integer, method as Integer, params_json as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Send an LSP notification message to the client
    Note: Notifications have no "id" field and expect no response
    Note: Used for diagnostics publishing, log messages, etc.
    Note: Format: {"jsonrpc":"2.0","method":"<method>","params":<params>}
    Note: Returns LSP_SUCCESS on success, LSP_FAILED on error

    If server is equal to 0:
        Return LSP_FAILED
    End If
    If method is equal to 0:
        Return LSP_FAILED
    End If

    Note: Build the notification JSON envelope
    Note: Allocate buffer for notification (4096 bytes max)
    Let notif_buf be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 4096
    If notif_buf is equal to 0:
        Return LSP_FAILED
    End If

    Note: Write JSON-RPC 2.0 notification structure
    Note: {"jsonrpc":"2.0","method":"
    Let write_pos be 0
    Note: Opening brace
    Let dummy_w1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with notif_buf, write_pos, 123
    Set write_pos to write_pos + 1
    Note: "jsonrpc":"2.0"
    Let jsonrpc_str_bytes be proc write_jsonrpc_header from notif_buf, write_pos
    Set write_pos to write_pos + jsonrpc_str_bytes

    Note: ,"method":"
    Let dummy_w2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with notif_buf, write_pos, 44
    Set write_pos to write_pos + 1
    Let dummy_w3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with notif_buf, write_pos, 34
    Set write_pos to write_pos + 1
    Note: Write "method"
    Let method_key_len be proc write_ascii_string from notif_buf, write_pos, 109, 101, 116, 104, 111, 100
    Set write_pos to write_pos + method_key_len
    Note: ":"
    Let dummy_w4 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with notif_buf, write_pos, 34
    Set write_pos to write_pos + 1
    Let dummy_w5 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with notif_buf, write_pos, 58
    Set write_pos to write_pos + 1
    Let dummy_w6 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with notif_buf, write_pos, 34
    Set write_pos to write_pos + 1

    Note: Write method name
    Let method_len be proc measure_string_length from method
    Let copy_idx be 0
    While copy_idx is less than method_len:
        Let mbyte be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with method, copy_idx
        Let dummy_wm be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with notif_buf, write_pos, mbyte
        Set write_pos to write_pos + 1
        Set copy_idx to copy_idx + 1
    End While

    Note: Close method value quote
    Let dummy_w7 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with notif_buf, write_pos, 34
    Set write_pos to write_pos + 1

    Note: Add params if provided
    If params_json is not equal to 0:
        Note: ,"params":
        Let dummy_w8 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with notif_buf, write_pos, 44
        Set write_pos to write_pos + 1
        Let dummy_w9 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with notif_buf, write_pos, 34
        Set write_pos to write_pos + 1
        Let params_key_len be proc write_ascii_string from notif_buf, write_pos, 112, 97, 114, 97, 109, 115
        Set write_pos to write_pos + params_key_len
        Let dummy_w10 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with notif_buf, write_pos, 34
        Set write_pos to write_pos + 1
        Let dummy_w11 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with notif_buf, write_pos, 58
        Set write_pos to write_pos + 1

        Note: Copy params JSON
        Let params_len be proc measure_string_length from params_json
        Let pcopy_idx be 0
        While pcopy_idx is less than params_len:
            Let pbyte be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with params_json, pcopy_idx
            Let dummy_wp be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with notif_buf, write_pos, pbyte
            Set write_pos to write_pos + 1
            Set pcopy_idx to pcopy_idx + 1
        End While
    End If

    Note: Closing brace and null terminator
    Let dummy_w12 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with notif_buf, write_pos, 125
    Set write_pos to write_pos + 1
    Let dummy_w13 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with notif_buf, write_pos, 0

    Note: Send the notification using the response sending mechanism
    Let send_result be proc send_response with server, notif_buf
    Return send_result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Internal Helpers - Response Building
Note: ============================================================================

Private Process called "build_initialize_response" takes request_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Build the JSON response for the initialize request
    Note: Contains full server capabilities declaration
    Note: Returns pointer to JSON string buffer, or 0 on failure

    Let buf be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 2048
    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Build the full initialize result JSON
    Note: We declare all capabilities that Runa LSP supports
    Let pos be 0

    Note: {"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":
    Let dummy_o be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 123
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let header_len be proc write_jsonrpc_header from buf, pos
    Set pos to pos + header_len

    Note: ,"id":
    Let dummy_c1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 44
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let id_len be proc write_json_key from buf, pos, 105, 100
    Set pos to pos + id_len
    Let dummy_colon be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 58
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let id_digits be proc write_integer_digits from buf, pos, request_id
    Set pos to pos + id_digits

    Note: ,"result":{"capabilities":{"textDocumentSync":1,
    Note: "completionProvider":{"triggerCharacters":[".","@"]},
    Note: "hoverProvider":true,"definitionProvider":true,
    Note: "referencesProvider":true,"documentSymbolProvider":true,
    Note: "renameProvider":true}}
    Note: Write result object with capabilities
    Let result_str_bytes be proc write_capabilities_json from buf, pos
    Set pos to pos + result_str_bytes

    Note: Close the root object
    Let dummy_close be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 125
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_null be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 0

    Return buf
End Process

Private Process called "build_null_response" takes request_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Build a JSON-RPC response with null result
    Note: Used for shutdown and other requests that return no data
    Note: Returns pointer to JSON string buffer, or 0 on failure

    Let buf be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 256
    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let pos be 0

    Note: {"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":
    Let dummy_o be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 123
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let header_len be proc write_jsonrpc_header from buf, pos
    Set pos to pos + header_len

    Note: ,"id":
    Let dummy_c1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 44
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let id_len be proc write_json_key from buf, pos, 105, 100
    Set pos to pos + id_len
    Let dummy_colon be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 58
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let id_digits be proc write_integer_digits from buf, pos, request_id
    Set pos to pos + id_digits

    Note: ,"result":null}
    Let dummy_c2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 44
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Note: "result"
    Let res_len be proc write_json_key from buf, pos, 114, 101
    Set pos to pos + res_len
    Note: Write "sult" to complete "result"
    Let dummy_s be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 115
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_u be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 117
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_l be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 108
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_t be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 116
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_q2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 34
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Note: :null
    Let dummy_colon2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 58
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Note: n=110, u=117, l=108, l=108
    Let dummy_n be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 110
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_u2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 117
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_l2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 108
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_l3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 108
    Set pos to pos + 1

    Note: Close object
    Let dummy_close be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 125
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_term be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 0

    Return buf
End Process

Private Process called "send_error_response" takes server as Integer, request_id as Integer, error_code as Integer, error_message as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Send an LSP error response
    Note: Format: {"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":<id>,"error":{"code":<code>,"message":"<msg>"}}

    Let buf be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 512
    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return LSP_FAILED
    End If

    Let pos be 0

    Note: {"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":
    Let dummy_o be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 123
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let header_len be proc write_jsonrpc_header from buf, pos
    Set pos to pos + header_len
    Let dummy_c be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 44
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let id_len be proc write_json_key from buf, pos, 105, 100
    Set pos to pos + id_len
    Let dummy_colon be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 58
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let id_digits be proc write_integer_digits from buf, pos, request_id
    Set pos to pos + id_digits

    Note: ,"error":{"code":
    Let dummy_c2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 44
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Note: Write "error" key and nested object with code
    Let err_key_len be proc write_json_key from buf, pos, 101, 114
    Set pos to pos + err_key_len
    Note: "ror"
    Let dummy_r be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 114
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_o2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 111
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_r2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 114
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_q be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 34
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Note: :{"code":
    Let dummy_colon2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 58
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_ob be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 123
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let code_key_len be proc write_json_key from buf, pos, 99, 111
    Set pos to pos + code_key_len
    Note: "de"
    Let dummy_d be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 100
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_e be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 101
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_q2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 34
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_colon3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 58
    Set pos to pos + 1

    Note: Write error code value (may be negative)
    If error_code is less than 0:
        Let dummy_neg be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 45
        Set pos to pos + 1
        Let abs_code be 0 - error_code
        Let code_digits be proc write_integer_digits from buf, pos, abs_code
        Set pos to pos + code_digits
    Otherwise:
        Set code_digits to proc write_integer_digits from buf, pos, error_code
        Set pos to pos + code_digits
    End If

    Note: ,"message":"Error"}}
    Let dummy_c3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 44
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let msg_key_len be proc write_json_key from buf, pos, 109, 101
    Set pos to pos + msg_key_len
    Note: "ssage"
    Let dummy_s be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 115
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_s2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 115
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_a be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 97
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_g be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 103
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_e2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 101
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_q3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 34
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_colon4 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 58
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Note: "Error"
    Let dummy_q4 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 34
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Note: E=69, r=114, r=114, o=111, r=114
    Let dummy_E be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 69
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_r3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 114
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_r4 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 114
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_o3 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 111
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_r5 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 114
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_q5 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 34
    Set pos to pos + 1

    Note: Close error object and root object: }}
    Let dummy_close1 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 125
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_close2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 125
    Set pos to pos + 1
    Let dummy_term be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with buf, pos, 0

    Let send_result be proc send_response with server, buf
    Return send_result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Internal Helpers - JSON Writing Utilities
